1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:40,000
(Watch on www.kisskh.li Support Admin)

2
00:00:42,731 --> 00:00:43,756
[This drama is a work of fiction.]

3
00:00:43,756 --> 00:00:44,795
[Any resemblance to real persons,
places, or events is coincidental.]

4
00:00:44,795 --> 00:00:45,817
[Scenes with child actors and animals
were filmed safely]

5
00:00:45,817 --> 00:00:47,552
[under professional supervision.]

6
00:00:47,552 --> 00:00:49,654
[Episode 8]

7
00:00:49,654 --> 00:00:51,615
Bang Tae Seop is gaining fast,

8
00:00:51,615 --> 00:00:53,908
[Bang Tae Seop goes all in for final push]
hot on Park Hong Jip's heels.

9
00:00:53,908 --> 00:00:56,147
Park Hong Jip holds 31.6%,

10
00:00:56,147 --> 00:00:58,580
Bang Tae Seop sits at 29.7%.

11
00:00:58,580 --> 00:01:01,666
With the Dongnam-gap race tightening,

12
00:01:01,666 --> 00:01:03,835
a growing number of polls forecast

13
00:01:03,835 --> 00:01:05,921
[Chu's boost narrows race to margin of error]
a win for Bang Tae Seop,

14
00:01:05,921 --> 00:01:08,632
and voters across the district
are up for grabs.

15
00:01:08,632 --> 00:01:11,355
Park's side is fighting to defend its lead,

16
00:01:11,355 --> 00:01:13,939
while Bang's team says momentum has shifted

17
00:01:13,939 --> 00:01:16,981
and goes on the attack.

18
00:01:18,875 --> 00:01:20,480
Every stock that's been falling apart

19
00:01:20,480 --> 00:01:23,613
bounces right back once you let it go.

20
00:01:27,495 --> 00:01:29,827
He keeps crossing my mind.

21
00:01:30,695 --> 00:01:32,663
Bang Tae Seop.

22
00:01:35,023 --> 00:01:37,501
Bang Tae Seop.

23
00:01:38,829 --> 00:01:40,879
[From Bang Tae Seop, Sir]

24
00:01:42,749 --> 00:01:45,188
Is someone watching me?

25
00:01:45,188 --> 00:01:47,546
Did someone put a camera in here or something?

26
00:01:47,546 --> 00:01:49,316
[Sir, here's an update on Lee Yang Mi]

27
00:01:57,806 --> 00:02:00,858
What is she pulling this time?

28
00:02:03,562 --> 00:02:06,231
[Bang Tae Seop]

29
00:02:06,231 --> 00:02:09,355
Bang Tae Seop...

30
00:02:09,355 --> 00:02:11,663
No.

31
00:02:11,663 --> 00:02:13,043
Absolutely not.

32
00:02:13,043 --> 00:02:14,707
If I reach out first, I lose.

33
00:02:18,397 --> 00:02:21,587
I was reckless back then.

34
00:02:25,023 --> 00:02:27,134
What is this?

35
00:02:33,158 --> 00:02:35,768
I do regret it.

36
00:02:36,928 --> 00:02:39,605
As you should.

37
00:02:39,605 --> 00:02:42,817
Trust me, I already do.

38
00:03:00,091 --> 00:03:03,851
Lee Yang Mi's up to something lately.

39
00:03:03,851 --> 00:03:05,500
You're really going to let that slide?

40
00:03:05,500 --> 00:03:07,511
Not a chance.

41
00:03:07,511 --> 00:03:11,213
That's why I'm teaming up with you
to bring her down.

42
00:03:11,213 --> 00:03:15,141
I've got all the paperwork you requested.

43
00:03:16,272 --> 00:03:19,230
That movie Lee Yang Mi's producing,

44
00:03:19,230 --> 00:03:21,441
it's budgeted at 30 billion won,

45
00:03:21,441 --> 00:03:24,564
but actual production spending

46
00:03:24,564 --> 00:03:26,098
comes in below 10 billion.

47
00:03:26,098 --> 00:03:28,105
So 20 billion just vanishes.

48
00:03:28,105 --> 00:03:31,866
That's Son Guk Won's slush fund money, right?

49
00:03:34,605 --> 00:03:36,655
With the presidency coming up,

50
00:03:36,655 --> 00:03:39,605
she's using the movie to clean cash?

51
00:03:39,605 --> 00:03:41,626
Exactly.

52
00:03:42,702 --> 00:03:46,540
One word of this hits the press, it's over.

53
00:03:46,540 --> 00:03:48,959
She chose Sang Ah
since there's no risk to her own people,

54
00:03:48,959 --> 00:03:50,897
and made her the sacrificial lamb.

55
00:03:50,897 --> 00:03:54,055
We use this to strike Lee Yang Mi first.

56
00:04:04,099 --> 00:04:06,768
Don't touch the film.

57
00:04:06,768 --> 00:04:07,772
Why not?

58
00:04:07,772 --> 00:04:11,841
Sang Ah catches shrapnel from that, too.

59
00:04:11,841 --> 00:04:15,068
Knowing the inside story is enough.

60
00:04:15,068 --> 00:04:18,030
We need something big enough to cover it.

61
00:04:20,198 --> 00:04:22,200
For now,

62
00:04:22,200 --> 00:04:25,203
arrange a sit-down with Assemblyman Choi.

63
00:04:25,203 --> 00:04:27,797
Assemblyman Choi? No problem.

64
00:04:33,647 --> 00:04:36,048
There's...

65
00:04:36,048 --> 00:04:39,975
something I've been working on quietly.

66
00:04:45,015 --> 00:04:46,933
Okay.

67
00:04:50,188 --> 00:04:52,947
The dust. Seriously.

68
00:04:53,564 --> 00:04:55,987
This dust is killing me.

69
00:05:03,897 --> 00:05:05,772
This isn't an abduction, right?

70
00:05:05,772 --> 00:05:08,045
What would I even do with you?

71
00:05:10,999 --> 00:05:13,085
The death of the Daeyang Fund CEO, Yoon,

72
00:05:13,085 --> 00:05:16,795
who built Son Guk Won's slush fund.

73
00:05:16,795 --> 00:05:21,593
That's always been Son Guk Won's weak spot.

74
00:05:21,593 --> 00:05:23,480
The party threw everything at it,

75
00:05:23,480 --> 00:05:26,981
but never found a way in.

76
00:05:30,939 --> 00:05:32,646
The day CEO Yoon was set

77
00:05:32,646 --> 00:05:34,815
to meet a reporter to expose Son Guk Won,

78
00:05:34,815 --> 00:05:36,858
he died in a car wreck.

79
00:05:36,858 --> 00:05:39,278
It was written off as sudden acceleration,

80
00:05:39,278 --> 00:05:42,057
but everyone suspected he was killed.

81
00:05:42,057 --> 00:05:44,272
Word was, there's someone called "the Shadow"

82
00:05:44,272 --> 00:05:47,678
doing all of Son Guk Won's dirty work.

83
00:05:47,678 --> 00:05:50,272
Right, we went after the Shadow ourselves,

84
00:05:50,272 --> 00:05:51,707
and came up empty.

85
00:05:51,707 --> 00:05:54,355
Here's the thing.

86
00:05:54,355 --> 00:05:56,586
We tracked him down.

87
00:05:56,586 --> 00:05:58,255
For real?

88
00:05:58,255 --> 00:05:59,688
This is Shadow intel

89
00:05:59,688 --> 00:06:02,133
from a senior prosecutor who dug

90
00:06:02,133 --> 00:06:04,719
into Son Guk Won at the time.

91
00:06:04,719 --> 00:06:07,897
[Evidence of Suspect Park Jae Hyun's
Illegal Transactions Uncovered]

92
00:06:08,605 --> 00:06:12,437
This individual
works as Son Guk Won's aide right now.

93
00:06:12,437 --> 00:06:14,479
This guy is the Shadow?

94
00:06:14,479 --> 00:06:16,989
98% sure.

95
00:06:19,439 --> 00:06:21,361
99%.

96
00:06:21,361 --> 00:06:25,011
The Shadow's exit records overlap

97
00:06:25,011 --> 00:06:28,702
with slush money routed to offshore accounts

98
00:06:28,702 --> 00:06:31,147
that dropped off the radar.

99
00:06:31,147 --> 00:06:34,749
That proves the Shadow works for Son Guk Won.

100
00:06:34,749 --> 00:06:37,188
So we frame the Shadow

101
00:06:37,188 --> 00:06:39,837
as the one behind CEO Yoon's death

102
00:06:39,837 --> 00:06:43,522
and pry open the Daeyang Fund slush.

103
00:06:43,522 --> 00:06:44,551
Now,

104
00:06:44,551 --> 00:06:49,064
if Bang hands that to the Changjo Party,

105
00:06:49,064 --> 00:06:51,224
the presidential race is already won.

106
00:06:51,224 --> 00:06:54,527
Naturally, that deserves something in return.

107
00:06:55,603 --> 00:06:58,739
As long as the source is solid, fine.

108
00:07:00,442 --> 00:07:01,985
For the general election,

109
00:07:01,985 --> 00:07:03,570
the party's full support

110
00:07:03,570 --> 00:07:06,772
plus Assemblyman Gu's rally appearances.
And then...

111
00:07:06,772 --> 00:07:08,742
I want a guarantee

112
00:07:08,742 --> 00:07:12,253
for the Chief of Staff position
in your camp for the next run.

113
00:07:17,230 --> 00:07:20,400
Why are you being so small-time?

114
00:07:20,400 --> 00:07:23,556
- Guess you don't want the intel.
- No.

115
00:07:27,397 --> 00:07:29,436
Done.

116
00:07:41,480 --> 00:07:45,035
Do me a favor before you retire.

117
00:07:47,322 --> 00:07:51,243
Step one, we convince the Shadow
that Son Guk Won sold him out.

118
00:07:51,243 --> 00:07:53,480
Splitting Son Guk Won

119
00:07:53,480 --> 00:07:56,873
and the Shadow apart, that's on you.

120
00:07:56,873 --> 00:07:58,740
[Son Guk Won:
Jae Hyun's been my shadow for a long time]

121
00:07:58,740 --> 00:08:00,845
[I've entrusted him with many tasks]

122
00:08:03,272 --> 00:08:05,055
By the way,

123
00:08:05,965 --> 00:08:10,540
how did you know I was drafting my resignation?

124
00:08:10,540 --> 00:08:12,639
You told me if they skipped you again,

125
00:08:12,639 --> 00:08:15,608
you'd walk away from the prosecution.

126
00:08:16,684 --> 00:08:18,019
[Assemblyman Choi Hak Sun]

127
00:08:18,019 --> 00:08:21,447
Pay him a visit. He'll give you a position.

128
00:08:25,355 --> 00:08:27,786
Okay.

129
00:08:32,700 --> 00:08:35,412
Just like old times.

130
00:08:56,064 --> 00:08:58,484
Hello.

131
00:09:00,561 --> 00:09:04,553
So, you're the legendary Shadow.

132
00:09:04,553 --> 00:09:07,326
What a pleasure to finally meet you.

133
00:09:17,397 --> 00:09:19,665
Once we pull forensics

134
00:09:19,665 --> 00:09:22,292
off the victim's phone, it all comes to light.

135
00:09:22,292 --> 00:09:24,760
So why don't we cut to it?

136
00:09:24,760 --> 00:09:27,439
We can prove you were on the phone

137
00:09:27,439 --> 00:09:30,724
with CEO Yoon just before his death.

138
00:09:32,886 --> 00:09:35,206
I have no idea what you're talking about.

139
00:09:35,206 --> 00:09:37,520
What's your point here?

140
00:09:37,520 --> 00:09:41,436
Forensics, whatever you want, be my guest.

141
00:09:41,436 --> 00:09:43,355
None of you

142
00:09:43,355 --> 00:09:45,906
can lay a finger on me.

143
00:09:50,361 --> 00:09:53,528
This time might be different.

144
00:09:53,528 --> 00:09:55,916
The person who gave you up?

145
00:09:58,522 --> 00:10:01,213
Came from your own side.

146
00:10:02,208 --> 00:10:04,803
The proof was strong enough

147
00:10:04,803 --> 00:10:08,721
to justify picking you up on the spot.

148
00:10:11,716 --> 00:10:14,097
[Assemblyman Son Guk Won]

149
00:10:19,144 --> 00:10:23,861
This guy keeps calling. So annoying.

150
00:10:41,639 --> 00:10:45,132
Calling Son Guk Won would be a mistake.

151
00:10:47,722 --> 00:10:49,397
Son Guk Won

152
00:10:49,397 --> 00:10:51,805
already cut you loose.

153
00:10:55,386 --> 00:10:56,897
You all

154
00:10:56,897 --> 00:10:59,981
have no idea who Assemblyman Son is.

155
00:10:59,981 --> 00:11:03,219
He'd never discard me this way.

156
00:11:03,219 --> 00:11:05,812
He'd have me killed.

157
00:11:05,812 --> 00:11:07,606
It's not the same this time.

158
00:11:07,606 --> 00:11:10,858
If I were him, with a presidential run ahead,

159
00:11:10,858 --> 00:11:13,187
I'd clean house with people like you

160
00:11:13,187 --> 00:11:16,864
who know where the bodies are buried.

161
00:11:16,864 --> 00:11:19,397
That locks down the presidency

162
00:11:19,397 --> 00:11:21,130
and the whole time in office,

163
00:11:21,130 --> 00:11:24,004
with nobody holding anything over him.

164
00:11:29,731 --> 00:11:36,702
The second Son Guk Won
rose as a contender, he was ready to drop you.

165
00:11:36,702 --> 00:11:40,064
CEO Yoon's accident, the timing was right,

166
00:11:40,064 --> 00:11:43,482
so he fed you to the prosecutors.

167
00:11:46,501 --> 00:11:49,235
Enough with the fairy tales.

168
00:11:49,235 --> 00:11:51,529
Keep playing loyal, then.

169
00:11:51,529 --> 00:11:54,981
You'll be the devoted mutt who saw it coming

170
00:11:54,981 --> 00:11:58,966
and still obeyed, only to get tossed aside,

171
00:11:58,966 --> 00:12:00,689
left to rot behind bars

172
00:12:00,689 --> 00:12:03,085
for the rest of your days.

173
00:12:08,041 --> 00:12:09,980
Look.

174
00:12:09,980 --> 00:12:12,086
The only way you walk out of here is

175
00:12:12,086 --> 00:12:16,041
if you turn over every piece of evidence.

176
00:12:16,041 --> 00:12:18,696
Son Guk Won takes the fall,

177
00:12:18,696 --> 00:12:22,855
gets a proper investigation.
That's your only move.

178
00:12:26,018 --> 00:12:29,855
If you had hard evidence I murdered CEO Yoon,

179
00:12:29,855 --> 00:12:31,953
you'd have come straight at me.

180
00:12:31,953 --> 00:12:33,731
None of these back-channel tactics

181
00:12:33,731 --> 00:12:37,654
would've been necessary, right?

182
00:12:37,654 --> 00:12:40,330
So what that tells me is,

183
00:12:41,635 --> 00:12:44,251
you're holding an empty hand.

184
00:12:48,188 --> 00:12:49,548
Well?

185
00:12:49,548 --> 00:12:51,466
Am I off the mark?

186
00:12:59,272 --> 00:13:01,435
Hey.

187
00:13:03,230 --> 00:13:06,916
This is my final offer

188
00:13:06,916 --> 00:13:09,568
to keep you alive.

189
00:13:14,939 --> 00:13:18,296
It's your call.

190
00:13:18,296 --> 00:13:21,064
And everything that follows,

191
00:13:21,064 --> 00:13:23,540
that's on you, too.

192
00:13:50,393 --> 00:13:52,182
A new chapter for Dongnam-gap.

193
00:13:52,182 --> 00:13:55,356
Cast your vote for Bang Tae Seop.

194
00:13:55,356 --> 00:13:58,522
[Gu Hong Seo, campaign chair,
stumps for Bang Tae Seop]

195
00:13:58,522 --> 00:14:00,028
- Bang Tae Seop!
- Bang Tae Seop!

196
00:14:00,028 --> 00:14:01,981
- Bang Tae Seop!
- Bang Tae Seop!

197
00:14:01,981 --> 00:14:03,614
- Bang Tae Seop!
- Bang Tae Seop!

198
00:14:03,614 --> 00:14:05,491
- Bang Tae Seop!
- Bang Tae Seop!

199
00:14:05,491 --> 00:14:08,790
[Changjo Party eyes first win]
- Bang Tae Seop! - Bang Tae Seop!

200
00:14:08,790 --> 00:14:12,753
[over Doyak in Dongnam-gap]
- Bang Tae Seop! - Bang Tae Seop!

201
00:14:14,480 --> 00:14:16,343
This way.

202
00:14:21,924 --> 00:14:25,144
[Full Script Reading and Production Ritual
for Four Seasons]

203
00:14:27,814 --> 00:14:30,065
Over here.

204
00:14:38,272 --> 00:14:40,575
Hello.

205
00:14:46,490 --> 00:14:48,375
- Hello.
- Hello.

206
00:14:48,375 --> 00:14:50,502
Thank you for making the trip.

207
00:14:53,647 --> 00:14:55,041
Why isn't she here yet?

208
00:14:55,041 --> 00:14:57,794
I've been trying to reach her.

209
00:14:57,794 --> 00:15:00,004
[Four Seasons, Hwang Jeong Won as Yu Hwa]
Are you sure you gave her the exact time?

210
00:15:00,004 --> 00:15:01,805
Yes, I am.

211
00:15:02,397 --> 00:15:04,558
But why would she...

212
00:15:56,939 --> 00:16:00,989
Now that we're all present,
let's start the read-through.

213
00:16:07,856 --> 00:16:10,689
There's an intimate scene
scheduled for the first day,

214
00:16:10,689 --> 00:16:12,796
which I realize is uncomfortable
for both of you,

215
00:16:12,796 --> 00:16:14,245
but the director thinks, emotionally,

216
00:16:14,245 --> 00:16:16,480
that rawness actually plays better on screen,

217
00:16:16,480 --> 00:16:19,549
so moving things around
wasn't really an option.

218
00:16:21,147 --> 00:16:23,220
It's fine by me.

219
00:16:30,887 --> 00:16:32,979
You're okay with it, right?

220
00:16:46,825 --> 00:16:49,454
I asked if you're okay.

221
00:16:51,772 --> 00:16:55,043
Well, I'm not.

222
00:17:01,147 --> 00:17:03,711
Did the director get lost?

223
00:17:03,711 --> 00:17:07,180
I'll step out for a second.

224
00:17:18,921 --> 00:17:20,902
Want a drink?

225
00:17:30,939 --> 00:17:33,206
How have you been?

226
00:17:35,605 --> 00:17:38,003
What about you, senior?

227
00:17:45,731 --> 00:17:47,762
Senior?

228
00:18:03,117 --> 00:18:06,136
Once that whole thing was over,

229
00:18:06,136 --> 00:18:09,151
I vanished, and you could breathe again.

230
00:18:09,151 --> 00:18:11,314
But now that I'm back,

231
00:18:11,314 --> 00:18:13,538
I guess it's hitting you.

232
00:18:26,188 --> 00:18:28,522
Yeah.

233
00:18:28,522 --> 00:18:30,764
It does hit different.

234
00:18:36,022 --> 00:18:39,022
I knew you'd show up someday,

235
00:18:41,797 --> 00:18:44,569
just didn't expect it to be like this.

236
00:18:55,397 --> 00:18:58,583
You were the one who wanted to work together.

237
00:19:24,144 --> 00:19:25,944
Tell me,

238
00:19:27,241 --> 00:19:30,365
what's your connection to Director Lee?

239
00:19:39,450 --> 00:19:42,647
What did she offer you

240
00:19:42,647 --> 00:19:45,922
to put you in this movie?

241
00:19:50,314 --> 00:19:53,738
What am I even capable of?

242
00:19:53,738 --> 00:19:55,890
You know who I am.

243
00:19:56,605 --> 00:19:58,685
And you know where I come from.

244
00:20:08,270 --> 00:20:10,272
[Case Summary Report]

245
00:20:10,272 --> 00:20:11,821
[Hwang Jeong Won fatally stabbed Yoon Chul Ho]

246
00:20:11,821 --> 00:20:13,546
[in the abdomen in a serious violent crime]

247
00:20:20,699 --> 00:20:24,647
[Crime Scene Photo, Exhibit No. 1]

248
00:20:24,647 --> 00:20:27,694
[Suspect Hwang confessed to the crime
immediately after her arrest]

249
00:20:52,731 --> 00:20:54,735
Chu Sang Ah...

250
00:21:00,023 --> 00:21:01,873
Ms. Chu...

251
00:21:05,397 --> 00:21:09,255
The same way you played
Park Jae Sang seven years ago,

252
00:21:09,909 --> 00:21:12,801
were you putting on a show for me, too?

253
00:21:18,647 --> 00:21:21,434
You were hoping I'd do

254
00:21:23,055 --> 00:21:25,855
exactly what he did, weren't you?

255
00:21:40,105 --> 00:21:41,892
I'm sorry.

256
00:21:41,892 --> 00:21:43,832
I'm so sorry.

257
00:22:19,695 --> 00:22:21,814
I've already briefed the Director,

258
00:22:21,814 --> 00:22:23,772
so just move forward with the plan.

259
00:22:23,772 --> 00:22:25,866
Yeah.

260
00:22:25,866 --> 00:22:28,661
Director, this is a late visit...

261
00:22:28,661 --> 00:22:30,494
First day on set, right?

262
00:22:30,494 --> 00:22:32,332
I'm here to cheer on the actors.

263
00:22:32,332 --> 00:22:33,707
That means a lot.

264
00:22:33,707 --> 00:22:36,253
- Everyone's doing well.
- Thanks.

265
00:23:04,411 --> 00:23:06,605
Ready.

266
00:23:06,605 --> 00:23:08,541
Action!

267
00:24:55,684 --> 00:24:57,352
Cut.

268
00:24:58,644 --> 00:25:00,187
Okay.

269
00:25:00,187 --> 00:25:03,483
That's good. Moving on to the next setup.

270
00:25:09,731 --> 00:25:12,689
That's solid material right there.

271
00:25:12,689 --> 00:25:14,077
Nice job, everybody.

272
00:25:14,077 --> 00:25:15,413
Strong first day.

273
00:25:15,413 --> 00:25:17,647
We've got a winner on our hands.

274
00:25:17,647 --> 00:25:19,207
Set up a nice gathering

275
00:25:19,207 --> 00:25:21,439
- and give the actors some praise.
- Sure.

276
00:25:21,439 --> 00:25:23,564
If there's anything you need,
just say the word.

277
00:25:23,564 --> 00:25:25,595
- You're doing great.
- Thank you.

278
00:25:32,719 --> 00:25:34,388
Well, if it isn't candidate Bang!

279
00:25:34,388 --> 00:25:36,515
Stopping by for your wife, as busy as you are.

280
00:25:36,515 --> 00:25:39,061
Thank you all for the hard work.

281
00:25:45,731 --> 00:25:47,314
Everything all right?

282
00:25:47,314 --> 00:25:49,571
Yeah.

283
00:25:49,571 --> 00:25:51,454
Hwang Jeong Won?

284
00:25:56,314 --> 00:25:58,503
Nice to meet you.

285
00:26:05,016 --> 00:26:07,255
Yes, nice to meet you as well.

286
00:26:07,255 --> 00:26:10,976
I've read about you and heard quite a bit.

287
00:26:10,976 --> 00:26:14,310
Same here. Your name comes up often.

288
00:26:15,896 --> 00:26:17,814
Please take care of...

289
00:26:19,064 --> 00:26:21,693
my wife on set.

290
00:26:25,897 --> 00:26:28,074
Of course.

291
00:26:32,946 --> 00:26:34,772
You must be cold.

292
00:26:34,772 --> 00:26:36,321
Yeah.

293
00:26:37,077 --> 00:26:39,502
How sweet.

294
00:26:50,981 --> 00:26:52,718
I'm turning down

295
00:26:52,718 --> 00:26:55,177
your offer.

296
00:26:55,177 --> 00:26:57,903
Where's all this confidence coming from?

297
00:26:57,903 --> 00:27:00,934
Whatever you've been doing, I told you.

298
00:27:00,934 --> 00:27:05,116
The higher you go, the worse the crash.

299
00:27:05,116 --> 00:27:07,780
You have a safety net lined up?

300
00:27:10,386 --> 00:27:12,751
Give it time, and you'll find out.

301
00:27:18,731 --> 00:27:20,746
Then again,

302
00:27:20,746 --> 00:27:24,630
a man who betrayed his own wife
will never change.

303
00:27:27,247 --> 00:27:30,422
Back in your prosecutor days,

304
00:27:30,422 --> 00:27:32,841
that legal fight
over Sang Ah's agency contract.

305
00:27:32,841 --> 00:27:34,716
What does that have to do with anything?

306
00:27:34,716 --> 00:27:35,844
You're the one who engineered that.

307
00:27:35,844 --> 00:27:37,167
All right.

308
00:27:37,167 --> 00:27:40,197
I set up the tax evasion leak, sure.

309
00:27:40,197 --> 00:27:42,431
But I looked into it,

310
00:27:42,431 --> 00:27:45,062
and you were aware of it all along.

311
00:27:45,062 --> 00:27:46,560
The Chief Prosecutor

312
00:27:46,560 --> 00:27:48,917
promised to promote you if you buried it,

313
00:27:48,917 --> 00:27:51,400
so you just swept it under the rug, right?

314
00:27:51,400 --> 00:27:53,195
Careful what you say.

315
00:27:53,195 --> 00:27:56,281
I stepped aside
because I had no way to fight you then.

316
00:27:56,281 --> 00:27:58,693
The game has changed.

317
00:27:58,693 --> 00:28:04,121
This time I've got a hand you can't beat.

318
00:28:04,121 --> 00:28:05,963
Is that so?

319
00:28:10,015 --> 00:28:13,638
You have no clue what cards I'm sitting on,

320
00:28:15,064 --> 00:28:16,496
and you're calling for a showdown?

321
00:28:16,496 --> 00:28:18,814
What's with you?

322
00:28:18,814 --> 00:28:20,305
Getting cold feet?

323
00:28:20,305 --> 00:28:22,897
If you're so sure, lay them on the table.

324
00:28:26,435 --> 00:28:29,773
I expected a tiger,

325
00:28:30,575 --> 00:28:33,902
but all I got was a stray pup.

326
00:28:33,902 --> 00:28:35,070
The general election,

327
00:28:35,070 --> 00:28:39,247
and Sang Ah's movie. Keep your hands off both.

328
00:29:11,229 --> 00:29:13,116
[Bang Tae Seop]

329
00:29:20,492 --> 00:29:22,915
Want to grab a drink?

330
00:29:38,105 --> 00:29:40,808
Come here.

331
00:29:41,897 --> 00:29:44,054
These are the people you'll be running with,

332
00:29:44,054 --> 00:29:45,550
[Changjo Party]
so get acquainted.

333
00:29:45,550 --> 00:29:47,766
Guan Yu, Zhang Fei, Zhuge Liang,
the whole crew's here.

334
00:29:47,766 --> 00:29:49,895
Good to meet you all.

335
00:29:49,895 --> 00:29:52,479
Sit down, please.

336
00:29:52,479 --> 00:29:53,772
- Get him a glass.
- Right away.

337
00:29:53,772 --> 00:29:55,457
- This is a sure thing, right?
- Absolutely.

338
00:29:57,194 --> 00:29:58,998
Thank you.

339
00:29:59,694 --> 00:30:00,862
Let's all have a drink.

340
00:30:00,862 --> 00:30:03,958
- Well done.
- Well done.

341
00:30:06,660 --> 00:30:09,188
We've got great energy.
Everything's going to work out.

342
00:30:09,188 --> 00:30:11,458
Seoam's Dongnam-gap continues
to be a fierce contest,

343
00:30:11,458 --> 00:30:13,925
with the outcome hanging by a thread.

344
00:30:13,925 --> 00:30:16,069
The latest survey results reveal

345
00:30:16,069 --> 00:30:19,549
only a 0.6-point spread

346
00:30:19,549 --> 00:30:22,571
separating the leading two candidates.

347
00:30:22,571 --> 00:30:26,390
[Seoam Dongnam-gap Poll Summary]
Doyak's Park Hong Jip stands at 32.2%,

348
00:30:26,390 --> 00:30:28,023
while Changjo's Bang Tae Seop

349
00:30:28,023 --> 00:30:29,808
[Park Hong Jip, Bang Tae Seop]
comes in at 32.8%,

350
00:30:29,808 --> 00:30:31,522
edging past Park Hong Jip

351
00:30:31,522 --> 00:30:35,905
in a contest that could go either way.

352
00:30:47,868 --> 00:30:52,831
After 30 years of defeat in this district,

353
00:30:52,831 --> 00:30:55,299
the unthinkable has happened.

354
00:30:56,856 --> 00:31:00,005
Bang Tae Seop has at last

355
00:31:00,005 --> 00:31:04,684
surpassed the Doyak Party in Dongnam-gap.

356
00:31:06,595 --> 00:31:08,265
- Bang Tae Seop!
- Bang Tae Seop!

357
00:31:08,265 --> 00:31:09,766
- Bang Tae Seop!
- Bang Tae Seop!

358
00:31:09,766 --> 00:31:12,066
- Bang Tae Seop!
- Bang Tae Seop!

359
00:31:13,345 --> 00:31:15,230
Thank you all!

360
00:31:15,230 --> 00:31:18,650
I'll carry this energy and write a new chapter!

361
00:31:18,650 --> 00:31:22,827
- Cheers!
- Cheers!

362
00:31:31,495 --> 00:31:33,428
[Unknown Caller]

363
00:31:35,230 --> 00:31:39,544
- Bang Tae Seop!
- Bang Tae Seop!

364
00:31:39,544 --> 00:31:43,216
- Bang Tae Seop!
- Bang Tae Seop!

365
00:31:46,015 --> 00:31:49,103
You wrecked a person's life,
and you're living large.

366
00:31:54,230 --> 00:31:57,115
You're the prick who hung
around Hwang Jeong Won, right?

367
00:31:57,115 --> 00:32:01,064
You pulled her into this in the first place.

368
00:32:01,064 --> 00:32:03,951
If something goes wrong,
you're the first one I deal with.

369
00:32:04,947 --> 00:32:07,621
Start with what's going on.

370
00:32:09,731 --> 00:32:11,814
Hwang Jeong Won

371
00:32:11,814 --> 00:32:14,922
got trapped because of the Park Jae Sang case.

372
00:32:14,922 --> 00:32:17,165
The casting, everything, it was all a sham.

373
00:32:17,165 --> 00:32:19,002
She walked right into a trap.

374
00:32:19,002 --> 00:32:22,839
Enough. Who has leverage on her,
and what is it?

375
00:32:22,839 --> 00:32:25,890
Spit it out, you piece of shit.

376
00:32:27,647 --> 00:32:29,062
Hey, hello?

377
00:32:29,062 --> 00:32:30,853
Hello?

378
00:33:40,435 --> 00:33:43,801
What was Bang Tae Seop to you?

379
00:33:53,731 --> 00:33:56,856
He was someone I owed a great deal to.

380
00:33:59,522 --> 00:34:01,694
Someone you owed a great deal to...

381
00:34:07,147 --> 00:34:08,951
Right.

382
00:34:09,925 --> 00:34:13,038
Even if we've ended up here,

383
00:34:14,105 --> 00:34:16,333
he and I both,

384
00:34:18,147 --> 00:34:21,380
we may have once been good people.

385
00:34:26,964 --> 00:34:30,598
Let me give you the answer

386
00:34:31,772 --> 00:34:33,726
to what you asked me then.

387
00:34:39,200 --> 00:34:42,318
When it came to Park Jae Sang, yeah...

388
00:34:43,731 --> 00:34:46,466
those feelings were real.

389
00:34:46,466 --> 00:34:51,327
To get away from the ones
who ruined me and my friend,

390
00:34:52,897 --> 00:34:55,064
I turned into something monstrous

391
00:34:55,064 --> 00:34:57,583
that devoured someone else.

392
00:35:06,195 --> 00:35:07,814
I believed if I suffered enough for it,

393
00:35:07,814 --> 00:35:11,507
I could finally get out.

394
00:35:11,507 --> 00:35:15,935
But when he caught up with me again,
I understood

395
00:35:17,355 --> 00:35:20,231
the only way out was death.

396
00:35:27,147 --> 00:35:29,448
That's the reason.

397
00:35:36,549 --> 00:35:39,910
If anyone discovered me,

398
00:35:39,910 --> 00:35:42,670
I hoped it wouldn't be Bang Tae Seop.

399
00:35:45,230 --> 00:35:47,758
I wished it'd be you instead.

400
00:35:55,856 --> 00:35:57,962
That's everything.

401
00:35:57,962 --> 00:36:00,604
Not sure that's the answer
you were looking for.

402
00:36:03,814 --> 00:36:05,776
Either way,

403
00:36:06,605 --> 00:36:09,196
no matter what my reasons were,

404
00:36:09,995 --> 00:36:12,853
I was only thinking of myself.

405
00:36:12,853 --> 00:36:14,827
I'm sorry.

406
00:36:18,897 --> 00:36:20,842
The reason I brought it up was

407
00:36:21,475 --> 00:36:25,337
I was afraid you were still blaming yourself.

408
00:36:28,105 --> 00:36:31,230
I chose to go there on my own,

409
00:36:31,230 --> 00:36:33,647
and I needed you to hear

410
00:36:33,647 --> 00:36:36,140
that none of it is on you.

411
00:36:59,772 --> 00:37:02,207
I'm sure this isn't news to you,

412
00:37:06,743 --> 00:37:09,757
but I went to kill Park Jae Sang.

413
00:37:34,814 --> 00:37:37,159
I need to use the restroom, give me a second.

414
00:40:28,740 --> 00:40:30,616
[Bang Tae Seop]

415
00:40:30,616 --> 00:40:34,211
[Find Sang Ah's location.
I'm asking if you found her]

416
00:40:37,248 --> 00:40:40,509
[Recents]

417
00:41:10,856 --> 00:41:13,083
Shit!

418
00:41:13,787 --> 00:41:15,961
This is fun.

419
00:41:18,500 --> 00:41:20,316
It's fun.

420
00:41:20,316 --> 00:41:21,771
Why did you kill him?

421
00:41:22,794 --> 00:41:24,626
Park Jae Sang.

422
00:41:32,023 --> 00:41:34,229
It wasn't me.

423
00:41:35,475 --> 00:41:38,066
But the way things stand,

424
00:41:41,636 --> 00:41:44,573
maybe it needs to be you who killed him.

425
00:43:17,074 --> 00:43:20,414
For me, Bang Tae Seop

426
00:43:20,414 --> 00:43:22,856
is more than a husband. He's my ally.

427
00:43:22,856 --> 00:43:24,923
He's my family.

428
00:43:25,519 --> 00:43:28,401
My father passed when I was little,

429
00:43:28,401 --> 00:43:32,133
and I was raised by a fierce single mom,

430
00:43:32,133 --> 00:43:36,131
so the meaning of family
and warmth was lost on me.

431
00:43:36,131 --> 00:43:39,023
He never stopped having faith in me,

432
00:43:39,023 --> 00:43:40,939
stayed right beside me,

433
00:43:40,939 --> 00:43:44,128
and rooted for me. Knowing that kind of bond,

434
00:43:44,128 --> 00:43:47,164
he's the one who taught me what that means

435
00:43:47,164 --> 00:43:49,614
for my life.

436
00:43:51,212 --> 00:43:52,689
So,

437
00:43:52,689 --> 00:43:57,914
what does your wife mean to you?

438
00:44:04,188 --> 00:44:06,241
Right from our very first meeting,

439
00:44:06,241 --> 00:44:10,257
I sensed something familiar in her.

440
00:44:10,257 --> 00:44:11,963
As our conversations deepened,

441
00:44:11,963 --> 00:44:14,924
I had this instinct that together,

442
00:44:14,924 --> 00:44:16,564
we could support one another

443
00:44:16,564 --> 00:44:20,503
through whatever came our way.

444
00:44:20,503 --> 00:44:22,348
If she hadn't been there,

445
00:44:22,348 --> 00:44:25,678
I wouldn't be the man standing here today.

446
00:44:25,678 --> 00:44:28,768
Though they once faced a scandal-fueled crisis,

447
00:44:28,768 --> 00:44:31,274
the pair's united front through hardship

448
00:44:31,274 --> 00:44:33,401
has been a major factor
driving his approval ratings.

449
00:44:33,401 --> 00:44:36,445
This wave of support
has deepened public confidence in Bang

450
00:44:36,445 --> 00:44:38,772
[Turning Crisis into Opportunity]
and appears to have cemented the arrival

451
00:44:38,772 --> 00:44:40,869
[Bang Tae Seop Leads in Dongnam-gap]
of the rising political force, Bang Tae Seop.

452
00:44:40,869 --> 00:44:42,785
Unless something unexpected occurs,

453
00:44:42,785 --> 00:44:46,004
this race appears to be Bang Tae Seop's to win.

454
00:44:52,564 --> 00:44:55,509
Rushing here right after work,
you must be beat.

455
00:44:55,509 --> 00:44:57,516
How about a beer?

456
00:44:58,814 --> 00:45:01,092
I'm shooting tomorrow.

457
00:45:01,092 --> 00:45:03,355
I'm wiped out. I'm turning in.

458
00:46:06,622 --> 00:46:11,173
Why Hwang Jeong Won disappeared
after the Park Jae Sang case...

459
00:46:13,814 --> 00:46:16,011
What's going on?

460
00:46:16,011 --> 00:46:19,831
If I don't do what they say,
they pin Park Jae Sang on me.

461
00:46:19,831 --> 00:46:22,851
One more murder rap, and it's over for me.

462
00:46:27,064 --> 00:46:30,163
Lee Yang Mi has dirt on her
and is pulling her strings.

463
00:46:31,855 --> 00:46:33,111
So?

464
00:46:33,111 --> 00:46:36,823
Do you have a read on how this is playing out?

465
00:46:38,024 --> 00:46:40,478
Do I have to spell it all out for you?

466
00:46:40,478 --> 00:46:43,572
Choi Ji Ho coming and going
from the set bugs me.

467
00:46:43,572 --> 00:46:47,125
So now that I've told you this much,
do something about it.

468
00:46:56,588 --> 00:46:59,272
The election's the day after tomorrow.

469
00:46:59,272 --> 00:47:01,806
Can you clean this up after it blows?

470
00:47:39,003 --> 00:47:40,799
Have you lost your mind?

471
00:47:40,799 --> 00:47:43,056
What the hell do you want from me?

472
00:47:46,439 --> 00:47:48,770
I've missed you.

473
00:47:51,981 --> 00:47:54,334
Since that day,

474
00:47:54,334 --> 00:47:57,362
I haven't gone one day without thinking of you.

475
00:47:58,885 --> 00:48:01,321
That night,

476
00:48:01,321 --> 00:48:04,619
if you believed I felt something for you,

477
00:48:06,230 --> 00:48:08,623
that was in your head.

478
00:48:12,453 --> 00:48:15,537
I was in pain, and I wasn't thinking straight,

479
00:48:15,537 --> 00:48:18,341
and all I wanted was someone to hold on to.

480
00:48:21,814 --> 00:48:24,389
Don't you want to break free?

481
00:48:26,939 --> 00:48:29,936
How much longer can you keep this up?

482
00:48:44,613 --> 00:48:47,454
Sorry, Director.

483
00:48:48,492 --> 00:48:50,814
End of roll.

484
00:48:50,814 --> 00:48:52,959
27, 10, 3.

485
00:48:57,522 --> 00:48:59,827
Are you feeling okay?

486
00:48:59,827 --> 00:49:02,761
I'm lightheaded. Give me a minute.

487
00:49:03,707 --> 00:49:05,439
- You all right?
- Let's take a quick break

488
00:49:05,439 --> 00:49:07,932
- and then get back to it.
- Are you okay?

489
00:49:27,197 --> 00:49:29,578
Your wife's routine has been normal.

490
00:49:29,578 --> 00:49:31,824
With your ratings going up,
WR looks like they're

491
00:49:31,824 --> 00:49:35,272
doubling down on her commercials
and the movie press.

492
00:49:35,272 --> 00:49:37,087
Understood.

493
00:49:44,003 --> 00:49:49,079
[Major Buzz: Sang Ah and Newcomer Jeong Won
to Star in "Four Seasons."]

494
00:49:53,355 --> 00:49:57,019
Why Hwang Jeong Won disappeared
after the Park Jae Sang case...

495
00:49:57,019 --> 00:50:00,443
Lee Yang Mi has dirt on her
and is pulling her strings.

496
00:50:07,814 --> 00:50:11,367
Whatever you've been doing, I told you.

497
00:50:11,367 --> 00:50:15,333
The higher you go, the worse the crash.

498
00:50:23,167 --> 00:50:24,230
Damn it.

499
00:50:24,230 --> 00:50:27,345
I can smell Lee Yang Mi all over this.

500
00:50:27,983 --> 00:50:30,716
I'm losing my mind over this.

501
00:50:30,716 --> 00:50:33,943
She's building up to something.

502
00:50:33,943 --> 00:50:38,023
Choi Ji Ho moving around
all of a sudden is shady, too.

503
00:50:38,023 --> 00:50:40,704
It feels like she's ready to hit Chu Sang Ah

504
00:50:40,704 --> 00:50:43,736
timed to the general election.

505
00:50:48,111 --> 00:50:51,073
Do we know when Lee Yang Mi plans to strike?

506
00:50:51,073 --> 00:50:52,303
Word from her inner circle is

507
00:50:52,303 --> 00:50:55,702
she's set to drop it on election day.

508
00:50:55,702 --> 00:50:57,565
Sang Ah may be the target,

509
00:50:57,565 --> 00:51:00,044
but I'm the one she's really after.

510
00:51:00,939 --> 00:51:03,538
She's trying to knock me out of the race

511
00:51:04,231 --> 00:51:08,303
so Son Guk Won can use me
as a shield through the presidential run.

512
00:51:09,345 --> 00:51:12,307
What about reaching out to Assemblyman Choi?

513
00:51:13,939 --> 00:51:16,806
The party isn't about to put itself on the line

514
00:51:16,806 --> 00:51:19,481
by taking on that level of exposure for me.

515
00:51:25,578 --> 00:51:27,981
If this election doesn't go my way,

516
00:51:27,981 --> 00:51:32,035
they'll milk the Shadow intel I handed over

517
00:51:33,090 --> 00:51:35,856
and throw me out.

518
00:51:35,856 --> 00:51:38,023
I'll get dropped without a second thought.

519
00:51:38,023 --> 00:51:40,335
Damn.

520
00:51:45,585 --> 00:51:47,084
If that's how Lee Yang Mi wants to play it,

521
00:51:47,084 --> 00:51:50,053
then I'm forced to take her on directly.

522
00:51:52,064 --> 00:51:54,776
I put my cards on the table

523
00:51:54,776 --> 00:51:57,602
and make her back down before she acts.

524
00:51:59,355 --> 00:52:01,935
So you want to use
the Son Guk Won Daeyang Fund card,

525
00:52:01,935 --> 00:52:05,272
now, in this race,
instead of holding it for the presidency?

526
00:52:05,272 --> 00:52:07,024
We're out of options.

527
00:52:07,024 --> 00:52:09,036
That's risky.

528
00:52:09,036 --> 00:52:10,676
Way too risky.

529
00:52:10,676 --> 00:52:12,917
